description.narrative:
Under the 5 outcome areas the following activities will be carried out:
-	Mapping and dissemination of information on available specialized SEC services for children;
-	Development, production and dissemination of IEC Materials on SEC;
-	Assist and provide PSS and other recovery support to victims of sexual exploitation;
-	Provide  Lifeskills training to victims and vulnerable girls and boys, young women and young men;
-	Link to potential employment opportunities through Department of Labor and Employment, Philippine Employment Service Office and Technical Education and Skills Development Authority;
-	Capacity-building, inclusion and participation of children and youth in the Local Council for the Protection of Children (LCPC);
-	Mobilize children and youth for agenda setting;
-	Consultations and dialogues with City Youth Councils, Local Government Unit departments, and Local Council for the Protection of Children;
-	Community orientation on SEC and its aggravating factors during the COVID-19;
-	Distribution of info materials in partnership with Barangay Local Government Unit officials;
-	Development and dissemination of information materials through social media platforms;
-	LCPC orientation on SEC prevention including reporting and referral mechanisms;
-	Conduct of financial literacy sessions;
-	Organize capacity-building and learning sessions on livelihood skills i.e. urban gardening, recycling and others;
-	Provision of post training support i.e. materials and mentoring support;
-	Dialogues with CPS actors to ensure the implementation of child-friendly COVID-19 response plans;
-	Orientation to enhance reporting, referral and coordination/collaboration  to different CSP actors;
-	Conduct gender sensitivity orientation among Child Protection System Actors;
-	Support policy advocacy work on SEC with Child Rights Network and Joining Forces Alliance;
-	Conduct policy review and recommendations for a harmonized SEC law and policies;
-	Support government-led celebration that encouraged private sector/industry participation in protecting children against SEC;
-	Collaboration with Joining Forces Alliance on EVAC, Child Rights Network, Civil Society Coalition on the UNCRC to lobby and advocate for the prevention, response and elimination of SEC

The Alliance sees capacity building as a key intervention strategy and achieves this in multiple ways. We continue to build the capacity of our implementing partners on e.g. gender (including implementation toolkit boys and SEC), child safeguarding and adaptive programming. We are strengthening the capacity and role of CSO’s, e.g. in influencing and holding duty bearers accountable, monitoring the implementation of child protection policies and gender responsive SEC response services. We are strengthening the capacity of local government actors to budget and implement policies in a gender responsive and inclusive way. We are strengthening the environment of children by building the capacity of families to provide care and protection. We are supporting communities to work together to protect children through community based child protection mechanisms. We are empowering children and youth to take on an active role in their own protection, strengthening their advocacy skills and peer-to-peer work. Lobbying & Advocacy is built into the programme at all levels, focusing on the urgency of the impact of the Covid-19 pandemic and building on the L&A achievements of 2016-2020. Where safely and meaningfully possible, children and youth collaborate with partners in advocacy, or even lead advocacy themselves. Together with, or led by our local partners, we aim to influence stakeholders at various levels. 

The programme will mobilize and influence parents, schools, community leaders and service providers to ignore this role in SEC prevention and response, including reintegration of victims and promotion of community based CPS. The programme will influence governments including LEAs and private sector actors through multi-stakeholder collaborations to jointly prevent and respond to SEC. We will influence regional and international intergovernmental bodies to prioritize the issue of SEC. We will bring local perspectives to the regional and international stage, and followup on international and regional developments in-country.
